    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="1362"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1362">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/7–2845</note>
                <head>No. 1362<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Aide-Mémoire</hi>
                </p>
                <p>His Majesty’s Ambassador at Paris<note n="1" xml:id="d1362fn1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_CAD1">Alfred Duff Cooper</persName>.</note> has been
                    instructed to inform the French Government that His Majesty’s Government are now
                    able to agree to the participation of the Soviet Government at the Paris talks
                    about Tangier and to suggest that the French and British Ambassadors in
                        Moscow<note n="2" xml:id="d1362fn2">General of the <persName
                            corresp="#p_CGAG1">Army Georges Catroux</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_KSAC1">Sir Archibald Clark Kerr</persName>,
                        respectively.</note> should be instructed to make a joint formal <pb
                        facs="1617" n="1419" xml:id="pg_1419"/> communication to the Soviet
                    Government, in reply to their representations in Paris and London of July
                        2nd,<note n="3" xml:id="d1362fn3">See <ref target="frus1945Berlinv01#d662"
                            >vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, documents Nos. 662</ref> and <ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv01#d663">663</ref>.</note> inviting them to
                    attend talks in Paris early in August.</p>
                <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_CAD1">Duff Cooper</persName> is further to inform the
                    French Minister for Foreign Affairs<note n="4" xml:id="d1362fn4">
                        <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Georges Bidault</persName>.</note> that, in line
                    with the previous assurance of His Majesty’s Government, the general question of
                    Tangier has not been discussed at Potsdam and that no reference will be made to
                    Tangier in the communiqué to be issued at the end of the Conference.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MGH1">G. H. M[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >iddleton</hi>]</persName>
                    </signed>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-28">July 28th,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
